<main>
    <section class="FAQs">
        <h1>Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ)</h1>

 <div class="faq-container">
        <!-- FAQ Item 1 -->
        <div class="faq-item">
            <div class="faq-question">What is the purpose of this application?</div>
            <div class="faq-answer">This application helps you manage your to-do list efficiently by allowing you to add, edit, delete, and track tasks.</div>
        </div>

        <!-- FAQ Item 2 -->
        <div class="faq-item">
            <div class="faq-question">How do I add a new task?</div>
            <div class="faq-answer">You can add a new task by clicking the "Add Task" button and filling out the task details.</div>
        </div>

        <!-- FAQ Item 3 -->
        <div class="faq-item">
            <div class="faq-question">Can I delete a task?</div>
            <div class="faq-answer">Yes, you can delete any task from your to-do list by clicking the "Delete" button next to the task.</div>
        </div>
    </div>

        <!-- FAQ Item 4 -->
        <div class="faq-item">
            <div class="faq-question">How can I change the status of a task?</div>
            <div class="faq-answer">You can change the status of a task by editing it from the to-do list page. Select the task, update the status, and save the changes.</div>
        </div>
    </div>

       <!-- FAQ Item 5 -->
        <div class="faq-item">
            <div class="faq-question">How do I log in to my account?</div>
            <div class="faq-answer">You can log in by clicking the "Log In" button in the navigation bar. Enter the credentials (username and password) on the login page to access your account.</div>
        </div>
    </div>

       <!-- FAQ Item 6 -->
        <div class="faq-item">
            <div class="faq-question">Is my data saved when I log out?</div>
            <div class="faq-answer">Y Yes, all your tasks and data are saved in the system, evening after you log out. You can log back in at any time to view or update your tasks.</div>
        </div>
    </div>
    
    </section>
</main>


